1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 9=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:38,160
Five.

4
00:00:38,750 --> 00:00:39,750
- The hand.
- Four.

5
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:40,750
Pull that hand.

6
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,790
- Three.
- Chubby, save me.

7
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:43,680
Two.

8
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:45,080
One.

9
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,960
There's a mechanism. Get down!

10
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,710
What are you yelling for?

11
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:08,790
Better safe than sorry.

12
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:11,430
Last time, I got shot.

13
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:02,870
Peng.

14
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:14,400
That big flame.

15
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:17,080
Why didn't you use it earlier?

16
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:18,750
Stingy.

17
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:37,030
Peng, what's on your neck?

18
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,190
- Peng.
- Peng.

19
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,430
- Peng.
- Peng.

20
00:04:01,590 --> 00:04:02,430
Are you crazy?

21
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:03,999
If that fuel bottle explodes,

22
00:04:04,010 --> 00:04:05,000
we'll all die.

23
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,200
Chen.

24
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:46,600
The finger and the base are linked.

25
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,830
When the finger bends,
a gap opens in the base.

26
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:49,950
The spiders come out.

27
00:04:50,270 --> 00:04:51,480
This isn't an exit mechanism.

28
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,320
You've been tricked.

29
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,390
These spiders attacked people

30
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:56,070
because they were trapped for too long.

31
00:04:56,229 --> 00:04:58,120
Once released,
their first instinct is to hunt.

32
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,390
That's survival instinct.

33
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,560
The biggest feature
of Tang Buddhist statues

34
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,000
is the folds of the lower robe.

35
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,270
They usually drape in front of the seat.

36
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,070
But this one is different.

37
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:21,790
I'll kill you.

38
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,320
What are you doing?

39
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,400
Don't move.

40
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:35,560
Can't we talk this out?

41
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:36,480
Talk about what?

42
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,390
If not for Chubby,

43
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,430
Peng wouldn't have died.

44
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:49,600
Come on.

45
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,630
Don't move.

46
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,240
Your boss triggered the mechanism.

47
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,600
Why hit Chubby?

48
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,005
If he hadn't given random orders,

49
00:07:01,016 --> 00:07:02,346
would those spiders have come out?

50
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,480
If he hadn't kept urging him,

51
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,120
would he have given those orders?

52
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,200
Huang Long.

53
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:10,750
Believe it or not, I'll shoot you.

54
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:12,150
Huang Long.

55
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,760
Stop.

56
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:16,270
This mission is tomb raiding,

57
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:17,120
not killing.

58
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:18,560
If you want to get paid,

59
00:07:18,745 --> 00:07:19,842
drop that mercenary attitude

60
00:07:19,853 --> 00:07:21,040
as soon as possible.

61
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:30,800
Yes,

62
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:32,270
madam.

63
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:56,270
Are you alright, Lu?

64
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,190
That scared me to death.

65
00:07:59,630 --> 00:08:00,480
Are you okay?

66
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,070
You two finally came back.

67
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:15,390
I can't catch my breath.

68
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:16,880
- The medicine?
- In the bag.

69
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,190
I told you earlier.

70
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:21,360
This isn't strolling
through an antique market.

71
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,800
I can't catch my breath.

72
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:25,390
My legs are weak. I'm nervous.

73
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,430
Do you have any other medicine?

74
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,430
No. Let me rest a bit.

75
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:35,080
He has low blood sugar.

76
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,280
Thanks.

77
00:08:40,150 --> 00:08:41,120
Wait, Miss Bai.

78
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,000
Anything?

79
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:45,480
You did save my life,

80
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,870
but what Mr. Li did

81
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:49,480
has killed one of my men.

82
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,030
We're even now.

83
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,320
Well.

84
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,480
If we're all square,

85
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,120
why don't you just get parted from us?

86
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:58,710
Cool.

87
00:08:59,000 --> 00:08:59,840
Wait.

88
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:04,240
Who was the man talking
to Chen on the phone?

89
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:07,270
Honey, is this your business?

90
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:09,200
How did he get the curse?

91
00:09:10,510 --> 00:09:12,440
And why did you lure him to this tomb

92
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,750
and pull all your strings?

93
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,240
Really want to know?

94
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,840
Continue the journey.

95
00:09:19,550 --> 00:09:20,390
Let's go.

96
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,150
There's a staircase going down.

97
00:10:32,390 --> 00:10:33,510
Here's one going up.

98
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:35,390
There's another staircase going down.

99
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:37,030
Another one going up.

100
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,670
Two up, two down. Four paths.

101
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:43,200
Which way do we go?

102
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,510
Show me some respect, and I'll tell you.

103
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,560
Mr. Li.

104
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:53,960
Alright then. I won't keep it from you.

105
00:10:54,270 --> 00:10:55,360
I really

106
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:56,510
don't know.

107
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,600
But I can let Mr. Chen tell you.

108
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,600
Mr. Chen, point us the way.

109
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,620
Which way should we go?

110
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,270
The magnetic field down here is strange.

111
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,750
The compass needle keeps spinning.

112
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:10,120
No, Mr. Chen.

113
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:11,720
I've already bragged about it.

114
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,293
If you fail me now, it won't look good.

115
00:11:14,019 --> 00:11:15,452
Do you even know what you're doing?

116
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,720
Stop talking nonsense.

117
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:17,720
Let me tell you.

118
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:18,790
Commander Chen's family

119
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,630
has ancestral skills.

120
00:11:20,910 --> 00:11:23,390
Three years to find the dragon,
ten to locate the spot.

121
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,120
Right, Commander Chen?

122
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:29,670
Think of something.

123
00:11:33,156 --> 00:11:34,989
Taiji divides
and establishes the two forms.

124
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,760
Yin and Yang spread,
following or reversing.

125
00:11:37,087 --> 00:11:39,233
Yin on the left and Yang on the right
form two paths.

126
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,390
Yang follows; yin reverses.

127
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:43,800
Did you hear that?

128
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:44,910
Did you all hear that?

129
00:11:45,670 --> 00:11:46,840
Do you understand it?

130
00:11:48,670 --> 00:11:49,550
Go on.

131
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:50,390
Don't stop.

132
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,150
If the compass fails,
we can't determine direction.

133
00:11:54,910 --> 00:11:56,510
If we can't tell the tomb's dynasty,

134
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:58,030
we can't determine its structure.

135
00:11:58,670 --> 00:12:00,200
Why recite all those formulas?

136
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,240
No, I...

137
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:02,720
Mr. Li, my foot.

138
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:04,120
What's wrong with you?

139
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,030
Watch how you talk.

140
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:06,390
Enough.

141
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,870
It's getting late.

142
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,670
We must find the main hall before 9 pm.

143
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:12,672
If we take the wrong path,
we'll just come back.

144
00:12:12,790 --> 00:12:14,630
Pick one and move out.

145
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,360
I choose that one.

146
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:38,960
Do you dare go?

147
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:45,960
I'll lead.

148
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,840
Stay behind and take care
of Ms. He and Lu.

149
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:56,960
Let's go, Lu.

150
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,870
Even you have helpless moments?

151
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:03,870
Sorry to make you laugh.

152
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,360
I'm not very knowledgeable.

153
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:07,270
Since you don't trust us,

154
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,390
why travel with us at all?

155
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:12,030
You know there won't be an answer.

156
00:13:12,270 --> 00:13:13,360
Why bother asking?

157
00:13:14,270 --> 00:13:15,390
I can only tell you

158
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:17,000
I'm not your enemy.

159
00:13:17,550 --> 00:13:20,390
So, please don't treat me
like an opponent.

160
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,030
- Count off.
- Lu.

161
00:13:25,030 --> 00:13:26,440
One. Two. Three. Four. Five.

162
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:28,600
Six. Seven. Eight. Nine. Ten.

163
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:29,750
Why are you shouting?

164
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:30,720
It's so dark.

165
00:13:30,930 --> 00:13:31,790
All of a sudden,

166
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:32,660
you did that.

167
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:33,550
How could I handle it?

168
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:34,496
You scared me to death.

169
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,320
Chubby, why 9 pm?

170
00:13:38,424 --> 00:13:40,148
Why must we find the main hall
before nine?

171
00:13:40,159 --> 00:13:41,399
Yeah, why?

172
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:43,510
Who knows
what Bai Lingling is planning?

173
00:13:44,030 --> 00:13:45,270
Go check on Chen Youxi.

174
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,510
I've got Lu.

175
00:13:46,521 --> 00:13:47,902
Who do you think Commander Chen is?

176
00:13:47,913 --> 00:13:49,283
Does he need me looking after him?

177
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:51,390
I'll smack you.

178
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:53,030
Just go as you're asked.

179
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:54,440
Why so much nonsense?

180
00:13:58,730 --> 00:13:59,600
Got it.

181
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,440
I'm going right now.

182
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:03,390
Be careful.

183
00:14:03,870 --> 00:14:04,720
I'm telling you.

184
00:14:05,390 --> 00:14:06,670
Don't take him seriously.

185
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,030
That kid is dumb.

186
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:21,960
Make way.

187
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,160
Chen.

188
00:14:24,223 --> 00:14:25,316
You should stay in the back.

189
00:14:25,327 --> 00:14:26,237
Why are you up front?

190
00:14:26,310 --> 00:14:27,150
I...

191
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:28,840
I'm following orders.

192
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:37,870
Miss Bai, be careful.

193
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:38,710
There are steps.

194
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,700
I'm not trying to scare you,

195
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:41,680
but listen.

196
00:14:41,910 --> 00:14:43,200
In tomb chambers,

197
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:45,320
the higher you go,
the more dangerous the steps are.

198
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,320
You know why?

199
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:47,790
Because there are fault gaps.

200
00:14:48,150 --> 00:14:50,120
If you fall into one of those gaps,

201
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:53,030
the fall will be horrific.

202
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,430
- Really?
- Yes.

203
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:55,630
But I think

204
00:14:55,630 --> 00:14:57,000
fault gaps won't affect you.

205
00:14:58,320 --> 00:14:59,160
Why?

206
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,440
Because

207
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:01,750
you'll get stuck.

208
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:04,350
Do I

209
00:15:06,910 --> 00:15:07,840
look that chubby?

210
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:09,790
Aren't you that chubby?

211
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,390
I can't walk anymore.

212
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:23,630
I can't catch my breath.

213
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,320
Let's rest a bit.

214
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:26,910
Hang in there.

215
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,510
We should find the exit soon.

216
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,080
Ms. He,

217
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:34,030
you've been encouraging me
this whole way.

218
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:35,960
Look how far we've gone.

219
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,480
We're almost at the ceiling.

220
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:39,440
And it still hasn't ended.

221
00:15:40,270 --> 00:15:41,320
It has ended.

222
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:09,110
Chen,

223
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:10,680
what's wrong?

224
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:31,230
This...

225
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,360
No, this...

226
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:44,200
This is where we came in earlier.

227
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:55,790
We were going in circles?

228
00:16:56,270 --> 00:16:57,110
No.

229
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:58,870
This is...

230
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,150
What is it?

231
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,440
The nether tomb.

232
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:21,070
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

233
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:26,430
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

234
00:17:27,490 --> 00:17:32,070
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

235
00:17:32,220 --> 00:17:39,220
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

236
00:17:39,780 --> 00:17:50,800
♪La la♪

237
00:17:57,550 --> 00:17:59,540
♪No line divides the border♪

238
00:17:59,980 --> 00:18:02,320
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

239
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:04,690
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

240
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:07,380
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

241
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,590
♪Hey hey hey♪

242
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:13,740
♪Hey hey hey♪

243
00:18:16,390 --> 00:18:17,390
♪Hey hey♪

244
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:18,540
♪Hey hey♪

245
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,080
♪Hey hey♪

246
00:18:22,710 --> 00:18:26,910
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

247
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:31,210
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

248
00:18:33,490 --> 00:18:35,710
♪No difference between you and me♪

249
00:18:35,990 --> 00:18:38,320
♪No lead or side role on this stage♪

250
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:40,530
♪A perfect life is something we share♪

251
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:43,030
♪Love declares across the sky and earth♪

252
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:48,750
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

253
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:53,600
♪Time and space go beyond all bounds♪

254
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:58,450
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

255
00:18:58,450 --> 00:19:00,540
♪This is our world♪

256
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:05,570
♪Shining lives bring the change♪

257
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:12,660
♪In a blink, to forever♪
